ot one set of legs. They have always dropped them before. Weird fluke, or has it been nerfed?<br>
<br>
I also have a warning - don't depend on faction to keep you safe in Skyshrine. I have been dubious for some time now there, and generally running around like I own the joint (at least away from Yelinak area, I am probably still KoS there). After doing spider quest the other night, I camped in Kale's room. The next time I logged on, every mob in the room was on me instantly and I was dead 30 seconds after I got in game (I checked my log, it was started by a gargoyle guard, and the rest joined in). When I got back, I was still dubious, and was able to loot my corpse right in front of the same critters that treacherously attacked. I petitioned this, hoping for a GM rez, and was told they could do nothing, it was not a bug.<br>
<br>
The GM would not expand on that, but the only way it could not be a bug that I can figure is that gsrgoyles are like centaurs - every so often they will attack despite acceptable faction. So now, I keep invis up in there anyway (in case of link death), and if I am inclined to camp in the zone, I do it where there are no roamers and out of aggro range. It is very annoying to get killed this way in a place you think you are safe. <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aelina>Aelina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 7:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Change in Skyshrine spider leg quest</span><hr size=1> I had the exact same thing happen to me with camping in Kales room.  It is an old bug.  What it is is sometimes when you log on for a brief second, long enough to agro mobs, you have your starting factions and not your current factions.  Though fortunately for me I have jboots and was able to make it to the zone before they all killed me, but I also got no help or even an explination from my petition.  The problem with the GM is they assume that a Yelinak faction mob walked by and agroed on you, causing the others to agro.  But don't belive that line man, it is a bug. <p><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>Aelina</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wizard of Neriak</td></tr>
<tr><td>Follower of The Burning Prince</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ayonae Ro</td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujetorian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jetorian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 1:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> leg quest</span><hr size=1> I've been doing the leg quest over the last week.  The legs are common, but dont always drop, you probably just had a string of bad luck.<br>
<br>
Never camp near a mob that used to be KoS to you, it takes a second or so before your faction hits get applied on zoning in.  I had the unfortunate case of zoning into SS while dubious only to have some 'friendly' hail holding the key quest drake at the zoneline while her friend rested up outside in WL.   I was not amused <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugherad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gherad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 1:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: leg quest</span><hr size=1> The spiders have never always dropped the legs.  Just most of the time.<br>
<br>
And the dubious mob killing you on zoning or camping is an old bug.  I haven't noticed it with higher factions though.  I am kindly in SS and I camp there all the time.  I can also port to WL safely all the time, even though my dubious friend is attacked due to the bug 1 out of 4 times.  Thank goodness for evacuate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uerruan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erruan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/01 8:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Change in Skyshrine spider leg quest</span><hr size=1> The reason they attacked you is because of &quot;Faction Lag&quot;... <br>
<br>
This usually only affects fast zoners, but it can affect anyone in theory, when you log in your faction files come up a second or two later then when you appear, so it reverts to your base faction until the files have loaded up... So basically if you were KoS somewhere by default, and you worked up your faction, if your Faction Files are lagging things will be once again KoS... So don't camp somewhere where you used to be KoS...<br>
<br>
Also GM's will NEVER give you a rez for this and will tell you that &quot;It's your own fault&quot;<br>
<br>
/sigh <p><CENTER><B><font face="Arial"><font color="#00CC00">Erruan (still no last name....)<BR>
